name: 8-hydroxy-5-deazaflavin:NADPH oxidoreductase
classes: Acting on the CH-NH group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
reaction: reduced coenzyme F420 + NADP+ = oxidized coenzyme F420 + NADPH + H+ [RN:R09749]
comment: The enzyme has an absolute requirement for both the 5-deazaflavin structure and the presence of an 8-hydroxy group in the substrate [1].

references.title: Characterization of an 8-hydroxy-5-deazaflavin:NADPH oxidoreductase from Streptomyces griseus.
